# Product direction

Read `docs/product/brief.md` before large feature work.

## Target

QA lead @ 11–100 person org. ReportPortal is the benchmark.

## Differentiators (equal weight)

1. **Correlation history** — same test across launches
2. **Substatuses** — nuance inside pass/fail/skip (e.g. passed-with-warning); see `docs/features/03-statuses.md`
3. **TypeScript dashboard plugins** — team-composed UI via low-ceremony plugins; see `docs/product/plugin-model.md`

## MVP golden path

JUnit adapter → REST API → UI (launches, substatus-aware dashboard, test detail, history/compare) + one TS dashboard plugin.

## In MVP

JUnit adapter v1, substatus on dashboard/history, plugin SDK + one slot + example plugin, Docker Compose, multi-project per instance.

## Out of MVP

SaaS, plugin marketplace, non-JUnit adapters, K8s/Helm, enterprise SSO.

## Success metric

One team (workplace pilot) uses every sprint without founder pushing.

## User stories

`docs/stories/mvp/README.md` — prioritize TR-010, TR-005, TR-011, TR-009 alongside TR-001.

